ls | sort -t'_' -k2 -h

If you have files numbered thus:

1370514827.3155_12.tcamuso
1370514827.3155_16.tcamuso
1370514827.3155_20.tcamuso
1370514827.3155_4.tcamuso
1370514827.3155_8.tcamuso
1370514828.3155_24.tcamuso
1370514828.3155_28.tcamuso

The above sort command will number them thus:

1370514827.3155_4.tcamuso
1370514827.3155_8.tcamuso
1370514827.3155_12.tcamuso
1370514827.3155_16.tcamuso
1370514827.3155_20.tcamuso
1370514828.3155_24.tcamuso
1370514828.3155_28.tcamuso

